1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,940
<i>Previously on</i> Kyle XY...

2
00:00:02,070 --> 00:00:03,437
Why are you acting so weird?

3
00:00:03,570 --> 00:00:05,820
Nicole says it's because I like you.

4
00:00:07,851 --> 00:00:10,110
- Don't you like me?
- Yeah, I do.

5
00:00:10,390 --> 00:00:12,204
My dad was notorious
for breaking promises.

6
00:00:12,324 --> 00:00:13,736
Don't wanna be that kind of father.

7
00:00:13,856 --> 00:00:15,758
You're not; you're a great father.

8
00:00:15,959 --> 00:00:17,042
My sister Jessi,

9
00:00:17,206 --> 00:00:18,731
she's been having some problems.

10
00:00:18,851 --> 00:00:20,622
We hope you might sit down with her.

11
00:00:20,742 --> 00:00:22,382
It's a really pretty necklace.

12
00:00:22,669 --> 00:00:25,067
Thanks. It's a remnant
from my Declan days.

13
00:00:26,769 --> 00:00:29,826
- Jessi, we're leaving.
- You can't tell me what to do!

14
00:00:34,074 --> 00:00:35,080
Foss!

15
00:00:38,774 --> 00:00:41,091
- I want to tell you everything.
- I'm ready to hear it.

16
00:00:43,458 --> 00:00:44,465
Foss did this?

17
00:01:01,406 --> 00:01:03,153
<i>Life is full of regrets.</i>

18
00:01:03,685 --> 00:01:05,716
<i>But no matter how hard you try,</i>

19
00:01:05,880 --> 00:01:07,722
<i>you can't change the past.</i>

20
00:01:09,412 --> 00:01:11,061
<i>Lori had been attacked.</i>

21
00:01:11,181 --> 00:01:13,399
<i>No one was sure who did it or why.</i>

22
00:01:13,814 --> 00:01:17,987
<i>And all I could focus on was how
I wasn't able to stop it from happening.</i>

23
00:01:22,930 --> 00:01:23,937
Hey.

24
00:01:25,199 --> 00:01:27,420
Dad, you have to stop doing this.

25
00:01:28,786 --> 00:01:31,596
And you, do I speak
with a British accent?

26
00:01:32,185 --> 00:01:33,191
No.

27
00:01:33,632 --> 00:01:36,071
- Am I wearing a crown?
- No.

28
00:01:36,679 --> 00:01:40,317
Then stop guarding my door
like I'm Queen freakin' Elizabeth.

29
00:01:41,404 --> 00:01:42,410
Sorry.

30
00:01:46,768 --> 00:01:48,173
He's just worried about you.

31
00:01:48,344 --> 00:01:49,464
I gathered.

32
00:01:49,996 --> 00:01:53,224
Sweetie, I know you're just
trying to be strong, but

33
00:01:54,116 --> 00:01:56,499
what happened, it's a lot to deal with.

34
00:01:56,651 --> 00:01:58,995
What happened is I became one
with my inner liberal

35
00:01:59,128 --> 00:02:00,643
and got hate-crimed for it.

36
00:02:00,909 --> 00:02:03,624
As far as I'm concerned,
this is my badge of honor.

37
00:02:03,785 --> 00:02:05,133
How's she doing today?

38
00:02:05,332 --> 00:02:06,700
Apparently, better than I am.

39
00:02:07,020 --> 00:02:09,791
- When I look at her it breaks my heart.
- I feel the same way,

40
00:02:09,911 --> 00:02:13,216
but we have to keep it together,
and make her feel safe and comfortable.

41
00:02:13,336 --> 00:02:16,114
How about whipping up
some sympathy pancakes?

42
00:02:16,627 --> 00:02:19,133
What? She likes them
and I'm in the mood.

43
00:02:19,958 --> 00:02:21,458
I'll be right down.

44
00:02:24,625 --> 00:02:25,631
Me first.

45
00:02:27,074 --> 00:02:28,099
All yours.

46
00:02:31,612 --> 00:02:33,428
I hope that's the police
with news for Lori.

47
00:02:33,548 --> 00:02:35,870
I already spoke to them.
Still no leads or eye witnesses.

48
00:02:35,990 --> 00:02:39,362
And since Lori can't identify her
attacker, then they're at a dead end.

49
00:02:39,489 --> 00:02:40,932
A Dr. Keel is on the phone.

50
00:02:41,425 --> 00:02:42,469
Dr. Keel?

51
00:02:42,870 --> 00:02:45,547
She's calling from the hospital
about a patient:

52
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:47,087
a William Trager.

53
00:02:48,625 --> 00:02:49,650
Who is he?

54
00:02:50,410 --> 00:02:51,729
He's my father.

55
00:02:52,109 --> 00:02:53,115
Hello.

56
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:54,990
Yeah, this is his son.

57
00:02:56,156 --> 00:02:58,415
I didn't know Stephen's father
lived in town.

58
00:02:58,585 --> 00:03:00,104
How long has he been sick?

59
00:03:00,237 --> 00:03:02,259
I don't know.
They haven't spoken in years.

60
00:03:04,145 --> 00:03:05,495
It's complicated.

61
00:03:08,019 --> 00:03:09,899
He had a stroke last night.

62
00:03:10,670 --> 00:03:12,716
Looks like he's not going to make it.

63
00:03:12,836 --> 00:03:14,202
I'm so sorry, Stephen.

64
00:03:15,158 --> 00:03:17,408
Is there anything I can do to help?

65
00:03:18,133 --> 00:03:20,878
No, there's nothing to do. I said
good-bye to my father years ago.

66
00:03:26,074 --> 00:03:27,785
Are things really that bad between them?

67
00:03:28,706 --> 00:03:31,572
I always hoped they'd manage
to repair things, but

68
00:03:31,862 --> 00:03:33,579
doesn't look like
that's going to happen.

69
00:03:34,686 --> 00:03:37,292
<i>Adam Baylin said
I would touch the world,</i>

70
00:03:37,647 --> 00:03:39,731
but what good is having a gift
if I couldn't help

71
00:03:39,851 --> 00:03:41,785
the people I loved the most?

72
